devdoc.details: The contract is built to be compatible with most ERC721 and ERC20 tokens.

params._nftCollection: - The address of the ERC721 Collection.
params._rewardsToken: - The address of the ERC20 Reward Token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setRewardsPerHour(uint256).details: Because the rewards are calculated passively, the owner has to first update the rewards to all the stakers, witch could result in very heavy load and expensive transactions or even reverting due to reaching the gas limit per block.

params._newValue: - The new value of the rewardsPerHour variable.

stake(uint256[]).details: Each Token Id must be approved for transfer by the user before calling this function.

params._tokenIds: - The array of Token Ids to stake.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

returns._availableRewards: - The available rewards for the user.
returns._stakedTokenIds: - The array of Token Ids staked by the user.

params._tokenIds: - The array of Token Ids to withdraw.

nftCollection.details: The ERC721 Collection that will be staked.

rewardsPerHour.details: The amount of ERC20 Reward Tokens accrued per hour.

rewardsToken.details: The ERC20 Reward Token that will be distributed to stakers.

stakerAddress.details: Mapping of Token Id to staker address.

stakerToArrayIndex.details: Mapping of stakers addresses to their index in the stakersArray.

stakers.details: Mapping of stakers to their staking info.

userdoc.notice: This contract uses a simple principle to alow users to stake ERC721 Tokens and earn ERC20 Reward Tokens distributed by the owner of the contract. Each time a user stakes or withdraws a new Token Id, the contract will store the time of the transaction and the amount of ERC20 Reward Tokens that the user has earned up to that point (based on the amount of time that has passed since the last transaction, the amount of Tokens staked and the amount of ERC20 Reward Tokens distributed per hour so that the amount of ERC20 Reward Tokens earned by the user is always distributed accounting for how many ERC721 Tokens he has staked at that particular moment. The user can claim the ERC20 Reward Tokens at any time by calling the claimRewards function.
